text: The family is originally Armenian ethnic. They used to live in Erzurum in Ottoman Empire (now modern Turkey). Kardashians first moved to Unites States in 1913. During Ottoman Empire, all Armenians used to have -yan adding to their last names and Kardaş-yan (in English version Kardashian), -ş is a sound of -sh. Originally Kardaş means unisex noun for people from same mother (brother/sister). So they still use Turkish last name.
title: What does Kardashian mean?
